column18: Transcribe the written answer of each participant's guess  of the study's goal.
I think the purpose of this was to test peoples motor skills and to see how peoples brains work when having to do something we notmall don’t do that is odd to us
I think the purpose of this experiment was to see the different ways we can use our bodies that are typically not used for certain tasks. like writing with our mouths.

To see if it is possible to perform these task using only your mouth. This experiment is to tell whether or not it is possible to do motor task. This is helpful as this is what disable people or people w/ disabilities have to adapt to.
I think the purpose was to find out which personality types are better or worse at completing tasks using methods that aren't seen as conventional.

To see how well our motor skills can adapt to things we normally don't do. This experiment was to see how we can use our motor skills with body parts that we don't usually use to do basic activities such as writing or drawing. What makes it more difficult is that the pen was unsteady. so it was tough to balance it in my mouth. However. if it was a smaller pen or pencil my face would be closer to the paper and allow me to have more balance and increase the ability for me to write.
To see how well a person can use a part of their body not normally used for a given task. and to see how easy or difficult it is to adjust to this new function.

The purpose of this experiment was to see how well I can use body parts that are rarely exercised in different ways. For example in this case it was to see how well we could use our mouths to write/draw.

I think the purpose of the experiment was to see how well we can use areas of our body. specifically our mouth that we don't normally use to perform a task like writing. To see how comfortable people are and to see if it's even possible.
I think the purpose of this experiment is to find out if it is possible for people with disability to write with a pen.

I think the purpose wsa to see how the pens in our mouths affected our motor skills and how we perceived the cartoons. The purpose of this experiment was to see how motor tasks such as holding a pen in your mouth effected your personality.

To see if a person is able to write by using mouth. Purpose is to observe if a person is able to use another part of body other than hands to write things down. Cartoons had to do w/ focusing on writing as well as trying to understand the cartoon.
To see how people with disabilities view things. This experiment was to test how well average beings are able to use things that are not for it's proper function. Personaly I think I have failed.
To determine if a task or stimuli would affect the quality of the motor skill. in this case the ability to use a pen with your mouth.
To see how disabled people resort to writing. I think the purpose of this experiment is to see how disabled people function (without arms) function while writing.
To write with your mouth.
To see how well people function when forced to use something or do something in a way they have never done it before.

To be able to see if disabled people/normal people could perform task without their hands. The purpose is to see how long or if people could perform tasks without their hands. or maybe follow instructions if you know you're being watched.

See how hard it is to write for people with no hands using their mouth. I do not really know what the purpose is. but I think it is to see if someone can become experienced in writing with their mouth.
The purpose was to see if we could use different body parts to carry out tasks that would normally be done with our hands.

I believe it is to show the difficulty of how difficult it is to use body parts one is not used to. For. say. a person missing limbs has to compensate writing with their mouth. feet. or a hand they are not familiar coordinating with.
The purpose was to see if we can successfully use other parts of the body to perform everyday tasks.

The purpose of this experiment is to see how well we can perform different taks in ways we would not do them on a daily basis. For example. connecting the two dots with the pen in our mouth instad of our hands.

I think the purpose was to see how effectively people  people can use other motor skills to perform taks they usually wouldn't do. It would be useful for people that are unable to use their hands to write or do other things.
I think the purpose was to analyze how we feel when struggling to say something we want to say.
The purpose of this experiment is to see how wel participants do when they're restricted to only writing with their mouths.

I feel that the purpose of this experiment was to see how humans are capable of adapting to performing basic tasks using unusual methods. It feels like it has something to do to see how well one can use an unorthodox way of doing a task on the spot without prior training/experience.

To look how long we can keep holding a pen with our mouth. Our daily life. ew don't keep opening our mouth more than a minute. By doing this experiment. researchers will know how long humans can hold a pen without touching lips. (Researcher will know when we are holding a pen with our lip. we are using muscle that we don't use during daily life).
To find an alternative way of writing and/or find ways or correlation between physical aspects and the personality tratis of some people.
I believe that the purpose of this experiment was to see how others can fair when they are not using body parts in which they are not familiar with to complete tasks.
I think the purpose of this experiment is to see if people can do everyday tasks without the use of an important body part.
To see if motor skills get in the way of thinking logically. I think the purpose of this experiment was to test the motor abilities when they are used at the same time as having to think logically.
The purpose of this exam wsa to see how people can use different parts of their body to perform tasks that were not normally performed by that body part.
By having a pen in your mouth. it's harder to have certain facial reaction as response to how funny the cartoon is.
To see the difference in coordination when using an unfamiliar part of your body to write.

To test the difficulty of holding a pen in your mouth and the correlations that can be drawn. To see how it feels to be disabled and have to write with your mouth. and the extent in which it affects the individual.
To determine whether or not people can function using body parts not normally used for ordinary tasks such as writing and drawing lines. Or even that of just holding a pen.

To view how and duration of time needed to sustain pen in mouth. To replicate the situation of individuals who have a disability where they are required to write with their mouth. Also to show how difficult it may be to hold the pen consistently.
To research other ways of writing other than using our hands.
To be able to test how people function without the capacity of using some body parts.
See how effective a person can be w/ a new task. The purpose of the study was to see how a person would perform a task that is foreign to them.
I think the purpose of the experiment was to help find ways people with motor deficiences find other ways of doing things they were used to doing in their past such as writing etc.
I think the purpose of this experiment is to help people understand that hands are a blessing and living life without hands can be very difficult.
To assess the ability of the brain to override natural urges (closing lips. using hands) and adapt.

Study motor skills that aren't always used. This experiment's purpose was to study motor coordination when placed in an uncomfortable position (e.g. holding the pen in your mouth instead of your hand).
To test motor skills with other parts of our body that we typically wouldn't use in certain situations.
To evaluate how people complete tasks that they would normally use with their hands and instead to use their mouth.
To see if we can substitute our hands with a different body part. and in this case it's our mouth.
To see how the psychomotor aspects of the brain are affected when we perform motor tasks we aren't used to doing with certain parts of our body.`
The purpose is to see if brain usage is affected by a pen being held by your mouth.

I think the purpose of this experiment was to see how people would perform normal tasks under different circumstances. I think that the purpose of this experiment was to see how people would perform normal tasks under different circumstances.

To see if people are able to use other body parts to perform tasks. The purpose of the experiment is to see if individuals are able to perform tasks with body parts that were not intended to be used for the task.
To determine the difficulty associated w/doing tasks that would normally involve using your hands
The purpose of this experiment is to test the participant by having them do an everyday task using a different body part and record their reaction to it.
Understanding other ways to write. To understand what other ways we could write. If someone can't use their hands. then another way to write would be better for them.
The purpose of the experiment was to see how motor functions do different tasks and how well a person can perform these unusual tasks that a part of their body doesn't normally do.

To test if holding a pen in your muth affects your thinking. The purpose was to test your skills with performing tasks with a pen in your mouth and if it influenced your responses on the third activity

The purpose is to find out if everyday simple tasks can be accomplished by using things other than a person's hands. Also. some stimuli/exercises may cause a person to drool more depending on how a person feels/thinks.
To see if people can use their mouth to perform tasks. See if using your mouth is another way to write with or do some tasks if the person is disabled and can not use their arms and hands.
The purpose of the experiment was to see the effectiveness of other body parts for tasks that require a different body part.
To see how well people can train themselves to not use hands. To help train people how to use a pen if use of hands is not an option.
column22: Product design and management for dance

column18: To test how well people can use their mouths to write.
The purpose of this experiment was to see if cognitive ability will be effected if you were try holding a pen in your mouth.
To determine the best way to perform motor tasks by using body parts not typically used for that task.
I think the purpose was to study how difficult it is to adapt under certain conditions.
I thinkthat the purpose of this experiment is to determine if people are capable of holding a certain position (pen in mouth) while performing mental activities simultaneously.
How resourceful one can get without using their hands.

To show how difficult it is for people with disabilities to carry on with their everyday lives. Of course this was on a smaller scale. but I think anyone would find it difficult to write with the pen being in your mouth. rather than your hand.
To see how humans are when they use parts of their body that they usually don't use mechanically in place of their hands.
To see how difficult it is to use other body parts for certain things. For people who don't have hands. we can see how difficult it is for them to perform certain tasks
To see how well people can perform writing tasks with their mouths.
Trying to accomplish things in a way we wouldn't to simulate how some people have to live through. This experiment wanted you to experience the difficulty in doing things in a way we aren't used to
To do stuff with a pen in your mouth. The purpose of this experiment was to do stuff with a pen in your mouth and see what it was like.
To find a writing alternative for people without hands. I think the purpose of this study is to find alternative methods for individuals without hands to write.
To see how easy or hard it was to use a pen with it in your mouth instead of hand.
To see how hard it is to use your mouth in place of hands to write.
To see how well someone could use another part of their body for something they aren't used to.

To determine whether or not you are able to perform tasks using another part of your body besides your hands. The purpose of this experiment was to see if tasks were able to be done without using your hands. In this case. it was to see if I was able to use a pen while holding it a certain way with my mouth.
The purpose of the experiment is to collect data on how individuals adapt to perform common tasks in unusual ways.

The experiment focused more on me holding the pen with my mouth. The first exercise is for me to practice writing with the pen and my mouth instead of my hand. However. I did not expect to have to be amused by the cartoons. I looked at the cartoons and I saw the images. some images were pretty normal and others were unusual. I focused more on me holding the pen correctly and writing with it. Therefore. I did not even pay attention at the meaning of the cartoons.
To see how well vocal muscles can perform a basic function. To see how a body part can perform a function it is not intended to do.
Stimuli that causes salvation. It was ask to perform these tasks with a pen in my mouth to see which task will cause salvation.

I believe this experiment was designed to make people aware of how difficult writing could be if you don't have your hads. This experiment was made so UNLV could maybe come up with ways to help disabled students write.
To better understand how we can use other body parts w/out having use of normal body parts. Somewhat to conquer functional fixedness possibly.
Using other body parts. For example. people without arms we can see how we can use other body parts for simple tasks.
The purpose of this experiment was to understand how motor skills are affected when controlled by different parts of the body.

I think that the purpose of this experiment was to understand and recognize the difficulty of having to write and use the pen with your mouth. It tested my quick ability to try and perform tasks that I usually would not need to do.
The purpose of the study is to assess the ability of the partiicpant to use their mouths to do task that are particularly done by the hand- in order to determine a person's adaptability.
The purpose of the experiment is to see how well we can use our mouths for other tasks.
The purpose of this experiment was to see how well our brain helps other body parts to do everyday tasks
The purpose of this experiment was to see how successful a person could be using a writing utensil with a part of their body they are not used to using
To evaluate people doing simple task with a challenge
Probably something to do with the cartoons and how you will interpret/understand them differently because of the concentration you have on holding the pen
To test how well we can use different body parts for tasks we normally wouldn't. Using the mouth for tasks we would normally use hands for. such as writing or drawing.
To see how well we follow directions. The purpose was to see how well we read the directions on each page and how we held the pen in our mouth.
`To show people how hard it is to be w/o your hands. Give people insight on how hard it is to do simple tasks like circling without being able to use your hands to help.
The purpose in my opinion was to show how difficult it is to use only your mouth as a form of writing.

If I had to guess. and from what I have been told. this experiment is either to see how it is people who do this every do do so successfully compared to us (me). Or to see how it is we can help them to perform the task of using your mouth for things you normally don't.
To see how we react when we use another body part to do tasks that we usually don't use them for.
See difficulty of controlling a pen with your mouth while using other motor skills.

The purpose of this experiment was to measure my accuracy when writing with a pen in my mouth. I was told the studies will benefit those who must use their mouths to write. because they are not able to use their hands.
I'm not so sure the purpose. I'm guessing it's probably to see how well humans can write with their mouth if they lose their arms.
The purpose of this experiment was to analyze psychomotoric skills.
To study how body parts have different purposes. To measure the accuracy of performance of tasks not completed through ordinary means.
I believe the purpose of this experiment was to view our mobility. or ability to use other resources to do a common thing besides our hands.

Answering basic problems. puzzles and questions using a form of written communication not normally used. Cartoons may try to employ more or different brain function to elicit mistakes with proper hold of pen in mouth.
To see how well one can use something other than their hand to write/use a writing utensil.

To see how well I can write with my mouth. (scratched out) perform a task without using hands.   Holding the pen in my mouth to write. To see how well I could perform the tasks asked without using my hands to write.

The purpose of this experiment is to held researchers identify how difficult or complex doing tasks are without the help of other body parts. It is to understand the importance of finding a way to complete certain tasks. as for those who do not have the ability to do so.

To understand or how people that cant use their arms/hands is like. Some people aren't able to use their hands or arms so it a great experiment to show how theirs another way they are able to do things. when not using their hands/arms.
To see how we move.

To see if we can perform motor tasks with different parts of our body. To see if we can perform a task such as using our moth to write. To measure or see how well we can perform motor tasks with uncommon parts of our body.
To study the difficulty writing in this way that some individuals may face everyday

To see how other body parts can be used instead of hands/arms. If a person loss movement/usage o ftheir arms. they can use other parts of their body. The experiment is collecting data to see how well mouths work in palce of hands.

To see how successful we were able to adapt to using different parts of our body to different applications we normally wouldn't use. I believe the whole purpose of this experiment was to see how well people adapt to using different parts of their body for performing tasks people normally wouldn't use that part of the body for. In this case. using a pen with your mouth instead of your hands. Probably. this study could help in coming up for solutions/technology for people who don't have hands or a certain limb.
To see how well people can communicate with a pen using hands. or using parts we normally don't use. To see how people do in preforming tasks that normally wouldn't be done with a certain body part.

I feel the purpose of this experiment is to learn how people w/ disabilities (ie amputations. paralyzations). have to use different parts of their body to perform regualr everyday tasks like writing. After having a disability for X amount of time. they may become used to writing/doing activities w/ other parts of their body to the point it becomes natural & they can write/do other things. as a person w/o disabilities could.

The purpose of this experiment was to identify the difficulties people without the use of their limbs might face when writing.  The difficulties can be helpful when creating other alternatives for people with this certain type of disability.
It helped us gain a new ability to do things with certain body parts that we usually wouldn't use for certain tasks.
The purpose of this experiment was to test abilities to do motor skills with their mouth and not their hands.

The purpose of the experiment is to see how we adapt to using muscles we don't commonly use to do tasks that are very normal to us. People that don't have arms commonly have to use these same muscles after they lose their limbs.

I think the purpose of this experiment is to show how different people are able to use other ways to write (not using their hands) and how challenging it may be because we are not used to it normally.
To see if we can write with a pen in our mouths. The purpose of the experiment was to see how well we are able to write with a pen in our mouth like instucted.
To see how well one can perform task w/ a pen in their mouth. To see how ones personality comes across while preforming task without their hands.
How well I can use my mouth to write with the pen.
Found an alternative way to write. The purpose of this experiment is to conduct research to see how many people are capable of using a pen in their mouth.
To better understand the difficulties people with disabilities go through.
To see if your activity is being effected by other physical impairments or difficulty.
To show how hard it can be for those who do not have the ability to write or perform activities with the convenience of hands.
To see how we complete tasks with other body parts. when we would normally use a certain one.

To see what ratings I gave the cartoons. I was told the purpose of the experiemtn was to see how well I could hold and write with a pen in my mouth but  I think that it was to see what I would rate the cartoons. I'm not sure how it relates but I think that rating the cartoons was the purpose of this experiment.
To see the difficulty of using a pen to write.
I think that being distracted by another task can also see what one's true personality is like.
To see how capable people would be in using their mouths versus their hands. Also to show how little we acknowledge what we can do/know.

When writing with a pen in your mouth. your observation of the page and its information is hindered. This test could possibly be testing for how much it (writing with our mouths) can affect our observation skills.

I believe the purpose of this experiment was to test if people could use different motor skills to perform certain tasks.  Also if people would be distracted by the pen in their mouth while reading cartoons.
To see how successful people are in performing tasks with a pen in their mouth

I think that the study's purpose is to see how we coordinate movement using parts of our body that we typically aren't used to using.  I know there are people that exist that can write with their mouths very well so this may be testing something like the power of repetition
To see if we can use things other than our hands to preform everyday actions.
To see how no-disabled people are able to perform tasks the way a person who is disabled might have to.
To test our ability to use other body parts to perform a task
To see how useful other body parts can be when the usual body parts made for certain functions are damaged or gone. This could also be used to see how difficult using nonpreffered body parts can be.
Evaluate altenative ways to do a simple task

To see how people use other body parts to perform tasks. To see how well we can perform tasks using body parts we usually don't use. And to see how well people can adapt to using other body parts to help with different tasks.
